Method Detail

getTargetHistoryToken

public String getTargetHistoryToken()
Description copied from interface: TabContentProxy
Gets the history token that should be accessed when the tab is clicked. In the fairly typical scenario where a tab directly contains a place, this should return the name token of that place. In the case of tabs that contain non-leaf presenters (for example, other tabs), this should return the name token of a leaf-level presenter. See NonLeafTabContentProxy.

Specified by:

changeTab

public void changeTab(TabData tabData)
Description copied from interface: TabContentProxy
Changes the data associated with this tab. This will automatically cause the displayed tab to change, provided the TabContainerPresenter containing this tab defines a ChangeTab field and passes it to the parent constructor.
